Аttached to the 
<taxonomicName box="[532,607,1146,1169]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[532,607,1146,1169]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">Cypris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[661,751,1145,1170]" class="Insecta" family="Mycteridae" genus="Cyclops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[661,751,1145,1170]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">Cyclops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the pools in the early spring (
<bibRefCitation box="[1114,1245,1145,1170]" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" refId="ref11213" refString="Kudo, R. R. (1931) Hand book of Protozoology. Springfield, Illinois, 451 pp." type="book">Kudo 1931</bibRefCitation>
); on the copepod 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[151,335,1181,1206]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Cyclopidae" genus="Eucyclops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agilis">
<emphasis box="[151,335,1181,1206]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">Eucyclops agilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation box="[387,700,1181,1206]" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" refId="ref10817" refString="Henebry, M. S. &amp; Ridgeway, B. T. (1979) Epizoic ciliated Protozoa of planktonic copepods and cladocerans and their possible use as indicators of organic water pollution. Transactions of the American Microscopical Society, 98, 495 - 508. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3225899" type="journal article">Henebry &amp; Ridgeway 1979</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
